Chord
public static class Chord.Modulus
extends java.lang.Object

The Modulus of a chord represents the number of tones in its octave. It exists in its most basic form at the Chord level.

mod

public int mod(int i)
Return the pitch class of the given note. For a 12 Modulus this means a number 0-11. For heptatonic work, it is 0-6.

Parameters:
i - a note, where C4 = 0, B4 = 11
Returns:
a number between 0 and OCTAVE_STEPS - 1

octave

public int octave(int i)
Return the octave of a given note. For 0-11, this is 4 (the middle octave), 5 for the next twelve and so on.

Parameters:
i - a note, where C4 = 0, B4 = 11
Returns:
the octave of the note (4)
